AGI - The first of the leaders to announce the descent into the field was Matteo Renzi. Matteo Salvini and Giuseppe Conte> have already said that they will not be at the starting strips of the race. Antonio Tajani has taken a step further: "I'm ready to run, I'll talk about it with my government allies, see what minister's commitments are. On April 20th at the National Council of Forza Italia I will explain the reasons in one case and another", the announcement of the secretary of Forza Italia. Between 15 and 19 will hold the national direction of the Pd with the secretary dem Schlein that should dissolve the reserve on its run.
From 26 to 28 April in Pescara will be held the FdI programme conference: it should be the event in which Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni could announce his candidacy as a leader in all the districts. Immediately after that date you should tighten on the television duel between the President of the Council and the number one of the Nazareno > that you should therefore 'distrust' in par withdicio regime (today the majority has deposited, among other things, the amendments to the deliberation set out by the Agcom, among other things, aims to review the criterion of the hourly bands with different "values" developed by the Agcom).
<div </div
&nbsp;
The final rush for the 8th and 9th of June started. And they continue their manoeuvres at the Centre: While Tajani and Lupi work on the understanding between FI and Noi Moderati, today Salvini and Cesa have announced a federation pact between the League and the Udc which also provides for the establishment of the parliamentary group of centrists in the Chamber.
The secretary of the blue party also announced during a press conference two new civic candidates in the lists of Forza Italia at Centro Italia: Graziella Ciriaci, entrepreneur from Marche, and Alessandro Ghinelli, mayor of Arezzo. "The objective of 10% is close," he said. The aim of the forziers is to overcome the League at the June meeting.
After the vote the game will open on the top of the European institutions. President of the EU Council? "It is a high-level personality but Member States must decide. Each decision must be taken after the vote. It is premature to speak of names," said the head of the Farnesina.
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The next president of the European Commission must be a representative of the Ppe, this is the only certain thing," said the Foreign Minister. Will it be Ursula von der Leyen even after the controversy? "Forza Italia respects the rules", and according to the polls "president will be you or another member of the Ppe", he cut short reasserting that he will talk about it "after the elections, probably in September. There's a lot of time."
While Salvini continues to reiterate his no to von der Leyen. "I expect concrete answers to citizens and Europeans, I think for example to fishermen, farmers and workers in the automotive sector, do not favor friends appointed as EU sent for SMEs," he remarked. The premier in the door-to-door study explained that the conservatives could also have a candidate for the Commission's presidency. "This is a decision we still have to make," he added. It will be in that case necessary to find agreement with the Poles of Pis and the occasion could arrive at the margin of the next European Council.
